abstract: Wall Street veered into the red as investors cashed their profits from a day earlier and waited for a highly anticipated report on January unemployment.

lead_paragraph: Losses in consumer stocks dragged Wall Street lower on Wednesday, while Bank of America stock fell below $5 a share, signaling more rough months ahead for the country’s largest financial institutions.

headline.main: Markets Close on a Down Note

abstract: Bank of America said Wednesday it was selling some of its corporate aircraft as the bank looked to scale back costs, The Associated Press reported.
